.\" swm.1 - Simple Window Manager manual page
.\" groff -man -Tascii swm.1   (to preview)
.TH SWM 1 "2026-03-13" "swm" "User Commands"
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH NAME
swm \- simple floating X11 window manager
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B swm
.RI [ config-file ]
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B swm
is a minimal floating window manager for X11.
Windows are placed freely on screen and can be moved, resized, focused,
and killed via keyboard chords or mouse gestures.
All behaviour is driven by a plain-text configuration file.
.PP
If no
.I config-file
argument is given,
.B swm
looks for
.I swm.conf
in the current working directory.
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH OPTIONS
.B swm
takes no flags.
The sole optional argument is the path to a configuration file.
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH CONFIGURATION
The configuration file is a plain UTF-8 text file.
Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments; blank lines are ignored.
.SS Settings
Each setting is written as:
.PP
.RS
.nf
key = value
.fi
.RE
.PP
The following settings are recognised:
.TP
.B terminal \fR= \fIcommand\fR
Program launched by the
.B spawn
action when no argument is supplied.
Default:
.IR xterm .
.TP
.B mod \fR= \fImodifier\fR
Modifier key used in all key bindings.
Modifiers can be chained without spaces, for example
.IR mod4shift .
Recognised tokens:
.BR mod4 " (Super/Win),"
.BR mod1 " / " alt " (Alt),"
.BR ctrl ,
.BR shift ,
.BR mod2 ,
.BR mod3 ,
.BR mod5 .
Default:
.IR mod4 .
.TP
.B border_width \fR= \fIpixels\fR
Border thickness drawn around every window.
Default:
.IR 2 .
.TP
.B border_color \fR= \fIcolor\fR
X11 colour (hex or named) of the border on unfocused windows.
Default:
.IR #3a3a3a .
.TP
.B focus_color \fR= \fIcolor\fR
X11 colour of the border on the focused window.
Default:
.IR #7a9fcf .
.TP
.B move_step \fR= \fIpixels\fR
Distance in pixels a window moves per keyboard step.
Default:
.IR 32 .
.TP
.B resize_step \fR= \fIpixels\fR
Distance in pixels a window grows or shrinks per keyboard step.
Default:
.IR 32 .
.SS Key bindings
Key bindings are written as:
.PP
.RS
.nf
key \fImodifier\fR \fIXKeysym\fR \fIaction\fR [\fIargument\fR]
.fi
.RE
.PP
.I XKeysym
is any symbol recognised by
.BR XStringToKeysym (3),
for example
.IR Return ,
.IR q ,
.IR Left ,
.IR f .
Run
.BR xev (1)
to find the exact name of any key.
.PP
The following actions are available:
.TP
.B spawn \fR[\fIcommand\fR]
Fork and execute
.I command
via
.IR /bin/sh .
If
.I command
is omitted, the value of
.B terminal
is used.
.TP
.B kill
Close the focused window.
Uses
.B WM_DELETE_WINDOW
if the window supports it; falls back to
.BR XKillClient (3)
otherwise.
.TP
.B focus_next
Move focus to the next window in the managed list.
.TP
.B focus_prev
Move focus to the previous window in the managed list.
.TP
.B fullscreen
Toggle fullscreen on the focused window.
Geometry is saved and restored on each toggle.
.TP
.B move \fIdx dy\fR
Move the focused window by
.I dx
pixels horizontally and
.I dy
pixels vertically.
Use negative values to move left or up.
.TP
.B resize \fIdw dh\fR
Resize the focused window by
.I dw
pixels in width and
.I dh
pixels in height.
Minimum window size is 64\(mu64 pixels.
.TP
.B quit
Cleanly exit
.BR swm .
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH MOUSE BINDINGS
The following mouse bindings are built-in and not configurable:
.TP
.BI mod " + left\-button drag"
Move the window under the pointer.
.TP
.BI mod " + right\-button drag"
Resize the window under the pointer from the bottom-right corner.
.PP
.I mod
refers to the modifier configured with the
.B mod
setting.
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH DEFAULT BINDINGS
Unless overridden by the configuration file, the following bindings are
active after a fresh install:
.PP
.TS
l l.
\fBmod + Return\fR	Open a new terminal
\fBmod + d\fR	Run dmenu_run
\fBmod + q\fR	Kill focused window
\fBmod + f\fR	Toggle fullscreen
\fBmod + j\fR	Focus next window
\fBmod + k\fR	Focus previous window
\fBmod + Left\fR	Move window left 32 px
\fBmod + Right\fR	Move window right 32 px
\fBmod + Up\fR	Move window up 32 px
\fBmod + Down\fR	Move window down 32 px
\fBmod + Shift + Left\fR	Shrink window width 32 px
\fBmod + Shift + Right\fR	Grow window width 32 px
\fBmod + Shift + Up\fR	Shrink window height 32 px
\fBmod + Shift + Down\fR	Grow window height 32 px
\fBmod + Shift + q\fR	Quit swm
.TE
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH FILES
.TP
.I swm.conf
Default configuration file, read from the current directory when no path
is given on the command line.
.TP
.I ~/.config/swm/swm.conf
Recommended per-user location.
Supply this path explicitly:
.PP
.RS
.nf
exec swm ~/.config/swm/swm.conf
.fi
.RE
.TP
.I /usr/share/xsessions/swm.desktop
Optional session entry for display managers such as
.BR lightdm (8)
and
.BR gdm (8).
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH EXAMPLES
Start
.B swm
with the default configuration file from the current directory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
swm swm.conf
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start
.B swm
from
.BR startx (1)
with a per-user configuration file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
echo "exec swm ~/.config/swm/swm.conf" >> ~/.xinitrc
startx
.fi
.RE
.PP
Test inside a nested
.BR Xephyr (1)
display:
.PP
.RS
.nf
Xephyr \-ac \-screen 1280x720 \-br :1 &
DISPLAY=:1 swm ~/.config/swm/swm.conf
.fi
.RE
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xev (1),
.BR xterm (1),
.BR dmenu (1),
.BR startx (1),
.BR Xephyr (1),
.BR xrandr (1),
.BR setxkbmap (1),
.BR XStringToKeysym (3)
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH BUGS
Mouse drag initiation requires the pointer to be over the window's client
area; grabbing via the border is not yet supported.
.PP
Only one X screen is managed.
Multi-head setups using separate DISPLAY values or
.BR Xinerama (3)
are not handled.
.PP
No ICCCM size hints (\fBWM_NORMAL_HINTS\fR) are honoured during resize;
terminal emulators may display fractional character cells.
.\"
.\" -----------------------------------------------------------------------
.SH AUTHOR
Written as a minimal reference implementation.
Patches and bug reports are welcome.
